# Prefer GOV.UK Frontend over axe

When accessibility tooling conflicts with the Design System, **GOV.UK Frontend wins**.

- Prefer official **GOV.UK Frontend** HTML (macros), CSS, and JS over changes driven solely by **axe** / **axe-core** (or similar automated a11y scanners)
- Do **not** deviate from GOV.UK Frontend markup, classes, attributes, or behaviour just to silence an axe rule
- If axe reports an issue that is inherent to official GOV.UK Frontend output or documented Design System patterns, treat that as an acceptable false conflict: document/disable the specific rule in tests if needed, rather than rewriting GOV.UK components
- Custom page composition may still follow axe guidance **only** where it does not alter or contradict GOV.UK Frontend components
- When investigating a conflict, verify against current GOV.UK Frontend docs and macros before changing UI code
